### PR summary [e2826eff5c](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/22552/commits/e2826eff5c058f9dfb2f2a4cdd124b3ffda926d0)

#### Import changes for modified files

No significant changes to the import graph


<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>

|Files|Import difference|
|-|-|

</details>

---

<details><summary>

#### Declarations diff

</summary>

`+ Ioc_disjoint_Ioc`
`+ Ioc_inter_Ioc`
`++ Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_of_le`
<details>
  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>


```bash
## summary with just the declaration names:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>

## more verbose report:
./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>
```
</details>

The doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.

</details>

---

<details><summary>No changes to technical debt.</summary>

You can run this locally as
```
./scripts/technical-debt-metrics.sh pr_summary
```
* The `relative` value is the weighted *sum* of the differences with weight given by the *inverse* of the current value of the statistic.
* The `absolute` value is the `relative` value divided by the total sum of the inverses of the current values (i.e. the weighted *average* of the differences).
</details>

I put `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_of_le` because it looks like [Set.Iic_disjoint_Ioc](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Disjoint.html#Set.Iic_disjoint_Ioc)  and I think this form is useful, so I added the same version for `Set`.

The variable `a` is already declared earlier in the file, so you only need `(d : α)` here. 
Do we also want to make `d` implicit?
I wrote `a` because I wanted `a` and `d` to be explicit as they are not in the hypotheses otherwise, but looking at lemmas around they should be implicit I guess.
Can you make this match `Set.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc`? and also put it in the same location within the file? Thanks!

[Set.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Disjoint.html#Set.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc) is about linear order while my version is about partial orders and is a bit more general than [Set.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_same](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/Disjoint.html#Set.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_same), so I changed the name and added a different `Finset.Ioc_disjoint_Ioc`.
This lemma doesn't exist for `Set`, and instead we have `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_same`
Note: I am not saying that `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_of_le` is worse than `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_same`. In fact I think it's better. However, sets and finsets should *definitely* have the same lemmas
I think it's not worth having `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_same` now. Can you deprecate it in favor of `Ioc_disjoint_Ioc_of_le`?

pullRequest.title: feat: ioc a b disjoint from ioc c d when a ≤ b
